    <item>
      <title>Demystifying AWS Policies with the IAM Policy Explainer Tool</title>
      <link>https://regblog.github.io/stem/iam-policy-explainer/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2025 00:20:29 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>https://regblog.github.io/stem/iam-policy-explainer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;AWS IAM policies are essential for securing cloud resources. However, they often contain multiple elements such as:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Actions&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., s3:PutObject, ec2:StartInstances)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Resources&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., S3 buckets, EC2 instances)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Conditions&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., specific tags, IP address restrictions)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here’s an example of a simple policy:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;{&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Version&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;2012-10-17&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Statement&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Effect&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Deny&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;NotAction&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;s3:PutObject&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Resource&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;arn:aws:s3:::example-bucket/*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Condition&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;StringNotEquals&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;aws:RequestedRegion&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;us-east-1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;      }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;While this policy is technically valid, its intent isn’t always clear to someone unfamiliar with AWS terminology.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Revolutionizing Live Sports Broadcasting: NHL and AWS&#39;s Cloud-Based Innovation</title>
      <link>https://regblog.github.io/stem/nhl-and-aws-cloud-based-innovation/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Mar 2024 20:50:38 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>https://regblog.github.io/stem/nhl-and-aws-cloud-based-innovation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The National Hockey League (NHL) has taken a significant leap forward in sports broadcasting by partnering with Amazon Web Services (AWS) to produce the first live game broadcast entirely from the cloud. This groundbreaking venture was showcased during the NHL Network&amp;rsquo;s Friday night coverage of the Capitals-Hurricanes game, marking a new era in the way live sports are produced and delivered.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;a-game-changing-collaboration&#34;&gt;A Game-Changing Collaboration&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The collaboration between the NHL and AWS utilized cloud technology to streamline the production process, reducing the need for a large on-site production crew. Instead, the only dedicated personnel at the game venue were AWS employees equipped with NVIDIA encoders, while the majority of the production team, including the director and crews for replay and graphics, operated remotely from the MLB Network studio in Secaucus. This innovative approach demonstrates the flexibility of cloud-based production, as the team could have been located anywhere with an internet connection.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Savings Account Calculator</title>
      <link>https://regblog.github.io/stem/savings-account-calculator/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 13 Mar 2024 08:47:07 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>https://regblog.github.io/stem/savings-account-calculator/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;label for=&#34;salary&#34;&gt;Salary (yearly):&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;salary&#34; value=&#34;103000&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;label for=&#34;savingsPercentage&#34;&gt;Savings Percentage (%):&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;savingsPercentage&#34; value=&#34;20&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;label for=&#34;apy&#34;&gt;APY (%):&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;apy&#34; value=&#34;4.35&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;label for=&#34;years&#34;&gt;Years:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;years&#34; value=&#34;30&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;label for=&#34;raisePercentage&#34;&gt;Annual Raise (%):&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;raisePercentage&#34; value=&#34;3&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;  &#xA;  &lt;button onclick=&#34;calculateAndGraph()&#34;&gt;Calculate and Graph&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;  &lt;canvas id=&#34;savingsGraph&#34; width=&#34;400&#34; height=&#34;200&#34;&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;    var chart;&#xA;    function calculateAndGraph() {&#xA;        var yearlySalary = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;salary&#39;).value);&#xA;        var savingsPercentage = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;savingsPercentage&#39;).value) / 100;&#xA;        var apy = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;apy&#39;).value) / 100;&#xA;        var years = parseInt(document.getElementById(&#39;years&#39;).value);&#xA;        var raisePercentage = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;raisePercentage&#39;).value) / 100;&#xA;      &#xA;        var monthlySalary = yearlySalary / 12;&#xA;        var monthlyContribution = monthlySalary * savingsPercentage;&#xA;        var monthlyContributionWithRaise = monthlyContribution; &#xA;        var monthlyInterestRate = apy / 12;&#xA;        var months = years * 12;&#xA;        var balance = 0;&#xA;        var balanceWithRaise = 0;&#xA;        var data = [];&#xA;        var dataWithRaise = [];&#xA;      &#xA;        for (var i = 0; i &lt;= months; i++) {&#xA;          if (i % 12 === 0 &amp;&amp; i &gt; 0) { &#xA;            monthlySalary *= (1 + raisePercentage);&#xA;            monthlyContributionWithRaise = monthlySalary * savingsPercentage;&#xA;          }&#xA;      &#xA;          balance += monthlyContribution;&#xA;          balance *= (1 + monthlyInterestRate);&#xA;          data.push({x: i / 12, y: balance});&#xA;      &#xA;          balanceWithRaise += monthlyContributionWithRaise;&#xA;          balanceWithRaise *= (1 + monthlyInterestRate);&#xA;          dataWithRaise.push({x: i / 12, y: balanceWithRaise});&#xA;        }&#xA;      &#xA;        &#xA;        if (chart) {&#xA;          chart.destroy();&#xA;        }&#xA;      &#xA;        var ctx = document.getElementById(&#39;savingsGraph&#39;).getContext(&#39;2d&#39;);&#xA;        chart = new Chart(ctx, {&#xA;          type: &#39;line&#39;,&#xA;          data: {&#xA;            datasets: [{&#xA;              label: &#39;Savings Over Time&#39;,&#xA;              data: data,&#xA;              fill: false,&#xA;              borderColor: &#39;rgb(75, 192, 192)&#39;,&#xA;              tension: 0.1&#xA;            }, {&#xA;              label: &#39;Savings with Annual Raise&#39;,&#xA;              data: dataWithRaise,&#xA;              fill: false,&#xA;              borderColor: &#39;rgb(255, 99, 132)&#39;,&#xA;              tension: 0.1&#xA;            }]&#xA;          },&#xA;          options: {&#xA;            scales: {&#xA;              x: {&#xA;                type: &#39;linear&#39;,&#xA;                title: {&#xA;                  display: true,&#xA;                  text: &#39;Years&#39;&#xA;                }&#xA;              },&#xA;              y: {&#xA;                title: {&#xA;                  display: true,&#xA;                  text: &#39;Balance ($)&#39;&#xA;                }&#xA;              }&#xA;            }&#xA;          }&#xA;        });&#xA;      }      &#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;  &lt;script src=&#34;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Mifflin St Jeor Calculator</title>
      <link>https://regblog.github.io/stem/mifflin-st-jeor-calculator/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Mar 2024 11:49:08 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://regblog.github.io/stem/mifflin-st-jeor-calculator/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id=&#34;calculator&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;label for=&#34;weight&#34;&gt;Weight:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;      &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;weight&#34; name=&#34;weight&#34; value=&#34;245&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;select id=&#34;weightUnit&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;lbs&#34;&gt;lbs&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;kg&#34;&gt;kg&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;label for=&#34;height&#34;&gt;Height:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span id=&#34;heightInput&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;height&#34; name=&#34;height&#34; value=&#34;71&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;select id=&#34;heightUnit&#34; onchange=&#34;changeHeightInput()&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;inches&#34;&gt;inches&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;cm&#34;&gt;cm&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;feetInches&#34;&gt;feet + inches&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;label for=&#34;age&#34;&gt;Age:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;      &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;age&#34; name=&#34;age&#34; value=&#34;22&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;label for=&#34;gender&#34;&gt;Gender:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;      &lt;select id=&#34;gender&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;male&#34;&gt;Male&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;female&#34;&gt;Female&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;label for=&#34;idealWeight&#34;&gt;Ideal Weight:&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;      &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;idealWeight&#34; name=&#34;idealWeight&#34; value=&#34;160&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;select id=&#34;idealWeightUnit&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;lbs&#34;&gt;lbs&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;        &lt;option value=&#34;kg&#34;&gt;kg&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;button onclick=&#34;calculateBMR()&#34;&gt;Calculate BMR&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button onclick=&#34;generateSpreadsheet()&#34;&gt;Download Spreadsheet&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;result&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;table&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Activity Level&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Calories/day&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td&gt;Base BMR&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;            &lt;td id=&#34;base&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Sedentary (little or no exercise)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td id=&#34;sedentary&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td id=&#34;lightlyActive&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td id=&#34;moderatelyActive&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td id=&#34;veryActive&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;        &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Extra active (very hard exercise/sports &amp; physical job)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td id=&#34;extraActive&#34;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;    function calculateBMRSpread(weight, height, age, gender) {&#xA;      &#xA;      if (gender === &#39;male&#39;) {&#xA;          return 10 * weight + 6.25 * height - 5 * age + 5;&#xA;      } else {&#xA;          return 10 * weight + 6.25 * height - 5 * age - 161;&#xA;      }&#xA;  }&#xA;  &#xA;  function generateSpreadsheet() {&#xA;      var weight = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;weight&#39;).value);&#xA;      var idealWeight = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;idealWeight&#39;).value);&#xA;      var weightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;weightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;      var idealWeightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;idealWeightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;      var height = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;height&#39;).value);&#xA;      var age = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;age&#39;).value);&#xA;      var gender = document.getElementById(&#39;gender&#39;).value;&#xA;      var heightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;heightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;  &#xA;      &#xA;      if (heightUnit === &#39;inches&#39;) {&#xA;          height = height * 2.54;&#xA;      } else if (heightUnit === &#39;feetInches&#39;) {&#xA;          var feet = Math.floor(height / 12);&#xA;          var inches = height % 12;&#xA;          height = (feet * 30.48) + (inches * 2.54); &#xA;      }&#xA;  &#xA;      &#xA;      var calculationWeight = weightUnit === &#39;lbs&#39; ? weight * 0.45359237 : weight;&#xA;      var calculationIdealWeight = idealWeightUnit === &#39;kg&#39; ? idealWeight : idealWeight * 0.45359237;&#xA;  &#xA;      var activityLevels = [&#xA;          &#34;Base BMR&#34;,&#xA;          &#34;Sedentary (little or no exercise)&#34;,&#xA;          &#34;Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week)&#34;,&#xA;          &#34;Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week)&#34;,&#xA;          &#34;Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week)&#34;,&#xA;          &#34;Extra active (very hard exercise/sports &amp; physical job)&#34;&#xA;      ];&#xA;  &#xA;      var activityMultipliers = [1, 1.2, 1.375, 1.55, 1.725, 1.9];&#xA;  &#xA;      var data = [[&#34;Weight&#34;]];&#xA;      activityLevels.forEach(function(level) {&#xA;          data[0].push(level);&#xA;      });&#xA;  &#xA;      &#xA;      var startWeight = Math.max(calculationWeight, calculationIdealWeight);&#xA;      var endWeight = Math.min(calculationWeight, calculationIdealWeight);&#xA;  &#xA;      for (var currentWeight = startWeight; currentWeight &gt;= endWeight; currentWeight -= 0.45359237) {&#xA;          var bmr = calculateBMRSpread(currentWeight, height, age, gender);&#xA;          var row = [weightUnit === &#39;lbs&#39; ? (currentWeight / 0.45359237).toFixed(2) : currentWeight.toFixed(2)]; &#xA;          activityMultipliers.forEach(function(multiplier) {&#xA;              row.push((bmr * multiplier).toFixed(2));&#xA;          });&#xA;          data.push(row);&#xA;      }&#xA;  &#xA;      var csvContent = &#34;data:text/csv;charset=utf-8,&#34; + data.map(e =&gt; e.join(&#34;,&#34;)).join(&#34;\n&#34;);&#xA;      var encodedUri = encodeURI(csvContent);&#xA;      var link = document.createElement(&#34;a&#34;);&#xA;      link.setAttribute(&#34;href&#34;, encodedUri);&#xA;      link.setAttribute(&#34;download&#34;, &#34;bmr_calculations.csv&#34;);&#xA;      document.body.appendChild(link);&#xA;  &#xA;      link.click();&#xA;  }&#xA;  &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    function changeHeightInput() {&#xA;      var heightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;heightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;      var heightInput = document.getElementById(&#39;heightInput&#39;);&#xA;      if (heightUnit === &#39;feetInches&#39;) {&#xA;        heightInput.innerHTML = &#39;&lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;feet&#34; name=&#34;feet&#34; placeholder=&#34;Feet&#34;&gt; &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;inches&#34; name=&#34;inches&#34; placeholder=&#34;Inches&#34;&gt;&#39;;&#xA;      } else {&#xA;        heightInput.innerHTML = &#39;&lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;height&#34; name=&#34;height&#34; placeholder=&#34;Height&#34;&gt;&#39;;&#xA;      }&#xA;    }&#xA;  &#xA;    function calculateBMR() {&#xA;      var weight = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;weight&#39;).value);&#xA;      var weightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;weightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;      var heightUnit = document.getElementById(&#39;heightUnit&#39;).value;&#xA;      var height;&#xA;      if (heightUnit === &#39;feetInches&#39;) {&#xA;        var feet = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;feet&#39;).value);&#xA;        var inches = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;inches&#39;).value);&#xA;        height = (feet * 12 + inches) * 2.54;  &#xA;      } else {&#xA;        height = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;height&#39;).value);&#xA;        if (heightUnit === &#39;inches&#39;) {&#xA;          height = height * 2.54;  &#xA;        }&#xA;      }&#xA;      var age = parseFloat(document.getElementById(&#39;age&#39;).value);&#xA;      var gender = document.getElementById(&#39;gender&#39;).value;&#xA;  &#xA;      &#xA;      if (weightUnit === &#39;lbs&#39;) {&#xA;        weight = weight * 0.45359237;  &#xA;      }&#xA;  &#xA;      var bmr;&#xA;      if (gender === &#39;male&#39;) {&#xA;        bmr = 10 * weight + 6.25 * height - 5 * age + 5;&#xA;      } else {&#xA;        bmr = 10 * weight + 6.25 * height - 5 * age - 161;&#xA;      }&#xA;  &#xA;      var activityLevels = {&#xA;        &#34;Sedentary (little or no exercise)&#34;: 1.2,&#xA;        &#34;Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week)&#34;: 1.375,&#xA;        &#34;Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week)&#34;: 1.55,&#xA;        &#34;Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week)&#34;: 1.725,&#xA;        &#34;Extra active (very hard exercise/sports &amp; physical job)&#34;: 1.9&#xA;      };&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;base&#39;).innerText = bmr.toFixed(2);&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;sedentary&#39;).innerText = (bmr * activityLevels[&#34;Sedentary (little or no exercise)&#34;]).toFixed(2);&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;lightlyActive&#39;).innerText = (bmr * activityLevels[&#34;Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week)&#34;]).toFixed(2);&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;moderatelyActive&#39;).innerText = (bmr * activityLevels[&#34;Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week)&#34;]).toFixed(2);&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;veryActive&#39;).innerText = (bmr * activityLevels[&#34;Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week)&#34;]).toFixed(2);&#xA;      document.getElementById(&#39;extraActive&#39;).innerText = (bmr * activityLevels[&#34;Extra active (very hard exercise/sports &amp; physical job)&#34;]).toFixed(2);&#xA;    }&#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;style&gt;&#xA;    table, th, td {&#xA;        border: 1px solid black;&#xA;    }&#xA;  &lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction-to-the-mifflin-st-jeor-equation&#34;&gt;Introduction to the Mifflin St. Jeor Equation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Mifflin St. Jeor equation is a widely used formula in the field of nutrition and dietetics to estimate an individual&amp;rsquo;s Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR). BMR is the amount of energy (in the form of calories) that a person needs to maintain basic physiological functions while at rest, such as breathing, circulation, and cell production.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Nature vs. Technology: the Path to Combating Climate Change</title>
      <link>https://regblog.github.io/stem/nature-vs-technology-the-path-to-combating-climate-change/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 Dec 2023 14:30:18 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://regblog.github.io/stem/nature-vs-technology-the-path-to-combating-climate-change/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In the ever-evolving dialogue on climate change, a critical question emerges: Should our focus be on harnessing the power of nature, such as through afforestation or advancing technological innovations in clean energy? In today&amp;rsquo;s Sustainability Saturday post, we delve into this debate, examining the potential and limitations of both natural solutions and technological advancements in our quest to cool the planet and reduce the impacts of climate change.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-case-for-nature-afforestation-and-beyond&#34;&gt;The Case for Nature: Afforestation and Beyond&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;understanding-afforestation&#34;&gt;Understanding Afforestation&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The concept of &amp;lsquo;afforestation&amp;rsquo; is essential to the conversation on natural climate solutions. It involves planting trees in areas that have lost or never had their forests. This approach is not just about adding greenery; it&amp;rsquo;s about reviving ecosystems and harnessing the inherent power of nature to combat climate change. Let&amp;rsquo;s delve deeper into its merits and challenges:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
